# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Identity Provider (IdP) configuration — REQUIRED
#
# Open Shortlink delegates user authentication to an upstream IdP. Configure
# EXACTLY ONE of the two modes below. If neither is set (or both are), the
# /authorize endpoint returns 503 and MCP clients cannot sign in.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Mode A: Cloudflare Access ---------------------------------------------
# Use this when the Worker's /authorize endpoint is fronted by a Cloudflare
# Access application. Access handles the sign-in flow and injects a signed
# JWT; we verify it against the team's JWKS and read the user's email.
#
# CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=acme.cloudflareaccess.com
# CF_ACCESS_AUD=<the AUD tag of the Access application fronting this worker>
# ACCESS_ALLOWED_EMAILS=you@example.com,teammate@example.com

# --- Mode B: Generic OIDC --------------------------------------------------
# Use this to delegate to any OpenID Connect provider (Auth0, Okta, Entra ID,
# Google Workspace, Keycloak, Authelia, etc.). The Worker acts as an OIDC
# Relying Party: on /authorize we redirect to the upstream IdP, and on
# /oauth/callback we verify the returned ID token.
#
# Register a new OAuth application at your IdP with:
#   redirect_uri = https://<your-worker>/oauth/callback
#   response_type = code
#   grant_type = authorization_code with PKCE
#
# OIDC_ISSUER=https://accounts.google.com
# OIDC_CLIENT_ID=your-upstream-client-id
# OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=your-upstream-client-secret
# OIDC_SCOPES=openid email profile
# OIDC_ALLOWED_SUBS=you@example.com,teammate@example.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# KV / Analytics Engine bindings are auto-provisioned by Wrangler on first
# deploy; no manual setup is needed for local dev.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Optional: Analytics Engine SQL query credentials.
# CF_ACCOUNT_ID=your-cloudflare-account-id
# CF_ANALYTICS_TOKEN=your-cloudflare-api-token-with-account-analytics-read

# Optional: comma-separated origin allowlist for CORS. Unset or `*` leaves
# every origin allowed. Set to a specific origin list when you publish a UI.
# CORS_ALLOW_ORIGIN=https://ui.example.com,https://admin.example.com

# Optional: canonical origin used in `shortUrl` responses and for edge cache
# purges. When the worker is bound to a custom domain, set this to the
# short-link host so responses don't echo the request host.
# PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://go.example.com

# Optional: host split. When both are set, the redirect host refuses
# /api/*, /mcp/*, and OAuth traffic, and the API host refuses /:slug traffic.
# REDIRECT_HOST=go.example.com
# API_HOST=api.example.com
